# Grants the EC2 instance permission to call Amazon Bedrock.
# Attach the managed policy via the instance profile in the EB console,
# or use the inline policy below as a starting point.
#
# Required IAM actions for the instance role:
#   - bedrock:InvokeModel
#   - bedrock:InvokeModelWithResponseStream
#
# The easiest approach: in the AWS console go to
# IAM > Roles > aws-elasticbeanstalk-ec2-role > Attach policies
# and add "AmazonBedrockFullAccess" (or a scoped-down custom policy).
